---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const title = "IAAWD mission | Support for disabled farm workers";
const description =
  "Read IAAWD's mission in plain English, including public-benefit advocacy, support for disabled agricultural workers, and public education.";
---

<BaseLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  path="/mission"
  breadcrumbs={[{ label: "Mission" }]}
>
  <section class="content-grid">
    <article class="page-panel">
      <p class="eyebrow">Mission and purposes</p>
      <h1>IAAWD&apos;s mission in plain English</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        The governing document describes a public-benefit mission centred on disabled
        agricultural workers and their family members.
      </p>
      <ul class="bullet-list">
        <li>Advance protection and welfare in agricultural settings.</li>
        <li>Support disabled agricultural workers and their families.</li>
        <li>Promote equitable legal and property rights.</li>
        <li>Encourage legislative change where rights need stronger protection.</li>
        <li>Educate the public and policymakers about disability-related barriers.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        This mission framing matters for SEO as well as for visitors. Searchers need
        to understand quickly that the site is about disability, agriculture, family
        impact, rights, and governance rather than a thin petition-only landing page.
      </p>
    </article>

    <aside class="quote-card">
      <h2>Public-benefit focus</h2>
      <p>
        The governing material points to support, advocacy, education, and
        collaboration rather than private commercial activity. That public-benefit
        framing should remain visible across the site.
      </p>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <section class="panel-grid">
    <article class="page-panel">
      <h2>What this means in practice</h2>
      <ul class="bullet-list">
        <li>Publish clear governance and contact information.</li>
        <li>Provide accessible summaries of key documents.</li>
        <li>Explain the rights themes raised by disability in agricultural settings.</li>
        <li>Make it easier for supporters and families to understand the issues.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="cta-panel">
      <h2>Continue through the site</h2>
      <p>
        The rights and support page explains the main advocacy themes. The resources
        page gathers the core public documents and links in one place.
      </p>
      <p class="mini-links">
        <a href="/rights-and-support">Rights &amp; support</a>
        <a href="/resources">Resources</a>
        <a href="/governance">Governance</a>
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
